# Documentation Requirements

**CRITICAL**: Documentation updates are MANDATORY for all code changes. This is non-negotiable.

## Pre-Commit Documentation Checklist

BEFORE EVERY COMMIT, you MUST update relevant documentation:

### 1. Update [docs/architecture-design.md](mdc:docs/architecture-design.md)
- Add new API endpoints
- Update service descriptions
- Document new configuration options
- Update performance benchmarks
- Add new security considerations

### 2. Update [docs/api-endpoints.md](mdc:docs/api-endpoints.md) (if backend changes)
- Update endpoint descriptions in code comments
- Ensure OpenAPI/Swagger docs are accurate
- Update API section in [README.md](mdc:README.md)

### 3. Update [README.md](mdc:README.md) (if setup/usage changes)
- Update installation instructions
- Update configuration options
- Update development setup steps
- Update any changed environment variables

### 4. Update Feature Documentation (if applicable)
- Create new feature docs in [docs/templates/](mdc:docs/templates/)
- Use template at [docs/templates/feature-requirement.md](mdc:docs/templates/feature-requirement.md)
- Update existing feature docs if functionality changes

### 5. Update [docs/performance-optimizations.md](mdc:docs/performance-optimizations.md)
- Document performance improvements
- Update benchmarks
- Document new optimization techniques

## What Requires Documentation

- New features or user-visible functionality
- Significant UX changes or navigation changes
- API contract changes
- Data model changes
- Security changes
- Configuration changes
- Performance optimizations

## What Does NOT Require Documentation

- Small bug fixes that don't change behavior
- Routine refactors with no functional changes
- Typo corrections in existing code
- Minor code cleanup

## Emergency Procedures

**If documentation is missing:**
- STOP the commit process
- Update ALL relevant documentation immediately
- Re-run the pre-commit checklist
- Only proceed after documentation is complete

Remember: Documentation updates are as important as the code changes themselves.